<h1>About Fitness Tracker</h1>

<section>
  <h2>Project Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Fitness Tracker is a web application designed to help users track their workouts, monitor nutritional
    intake, and track progress toward their fitness goals. Users can browse exercises, log workouts,
    record meals, and track their weight and other metrics over time.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Data Sources</h2>

  <div>
    <h3>ExerciseDB API</h3>
    <p>Exercise data is sourced from the ExerciseDB API, which provides comprehensive information about various exercises including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Exercise name</li>
      <li>Exercise type (strength, cardio, flexibility, etc.)</li>
      <li>Target muscle group</li>
      <li>Required equipment</li>
      <li>Difficulty level</li>
      <li>Instructions</li>
      <li>Demo image/GIF URL</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <strong>Source:</strong>
      <a href="https://rapidapi.com/justin-WFnsXH_t6/api/exercisedb" target="_blank">
        ExerciseDB API on RapidAPI
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>Foundation Foods CSV</h3>
    <p>Nutritional information is imported from the USDA Foundation Foods dataset, which includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Food item name</li>
      <li>Calorie content per serving</li>
      <li>Protein content (grams)</li>
      <li>Carbohydrate content (grams)</li>
      <li>Fat content (grams)</li>
      <li>Serving size information</li>
      <li>Food category</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <strong>Source:</strong>
      <a href="https://fdc.nal.usda.gov/download-datasets" target="_blank">
        USDA FoodData Central
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>Faker Gem</h3>
    <p>Generated user and workout data including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>User profiles (name, age, height, weight, fitness level)</li>
      <li>Workout logs (date, duration, exercises performed)</li>
      <li>User fitness goals and progress tracking</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Database Structure</h2>
  <p>The application utilizes the following database tables:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>users</strong> - User profiles and details</li>
    <li><strong>exercises</strong> - Exercise information and instructions</li>
    <li><strong>workouts</strong> - Workout plans and logs</li>
    <li><strong>workout_exercises</strong> - Join table connecting workouts and exercises</li>
    <li><strong>foods</strong> - Nutritional information for food items</li>
    <li><strong>food_categories</strong> - Categories for organizing food items</li>
    <li><strong>meal_logs</strong> - User's food consumption records</li>
    <li><strong>meal_foods</strong> - Join table connecting meals and foods</li>
    <li><strong>progress_entries</strong> - User's progress tracking data</li>
  </ul>

